pgTitle: List of Superfund sites in California

rows.text: El Toro Marine Corps Air Station

200,000 cubic yards of oil refinery acid sludge and oil field drilling muds, including sulfur and hydrocarbons. The wastes have reacted to produce a mixture of complex organic and sulfur-containing compounds, some of which are gases.
Mather Air Force Base (Aircraft Control and Warning Disposal Site)
Treasure Island Naval Station-Hunters Point Annex
Surface water is contaminated with sulfuric acid, copper, zinc, and cadmium from the mine.
Laboratory for Energy-Related Health Research/Old Campus Landfill
Groundwater and soil contaminated with solvents, chemical wastes, and radioactive wastes.

Contamination found on site includes a combination of several metals and radionuclides significantly above background. These contaminants include aluminum, arsenic, barium, beryllium, cadmium, chromium, copper, lead, magnesium, manganese, nickel, silver, zinc, cesium-137, potassium-40, thorium-228, thorium-230, and thorium-232.
Liquid and semisolid refinery wastes were dumped in unlined pits and sumps. Soil contains benzene, 1,3-dichlorobenzene, and lead.
